Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.89,0:00:04.83,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV radio production unit producer,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.83,0:00:10.44,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Manda Teruomi, is a superficial man\N who's been living off his glibness alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.24,0:00:07.06,Teruomi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Manda Teruomi (40) \NNichiuri TV & Radio \NProduction Unit Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.60,0:00:14.07,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,And Manda secretly murdered \Nhis estranged wife Towako
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.07,0:00:16.47,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}because she wouldn't agree to a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.87,0:00:17.58,Towako,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Manda Towako (31) \NHousewife
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.17,0:00:22.08,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Furthermore, he used the \Nradio show he produces
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.91,0:00:20.75,Laughing,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Now the whole world's laughing at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.08,0:00:26.94,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}to frame Towako's upstairs \Nneighbor, Kijima Kumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.91,0:00:24.37,Kumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kijima Kumi (38) \NHousewife
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.59,0:00:31.49,DCItalic,CULPRIT,0000,0000,0000,,However, he couldn't deceive \Nthe eyes of the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.53,0:00:35.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this a premeditated murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.16,0:00:39.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could Manda-san really have come \Nup with this if he's all talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.65,0:00:43.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He was just that desperate \Nto divorce his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.71,0:00:45.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yashiro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.13,0:00:45.81,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:50.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Those two seem to really hate Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.45,0:00:51.38,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.38,0:00:57.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying one of them did it \Nand is trying to frame Manda-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.71,0:01:00.45,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought it might be a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.50,0:01:11.00,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the boy suspects \Nsomething, it's too late
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.25,0:01:15.01,Plan,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Everything has gone according to plan
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.39,0:01:17.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You underestimate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.02,0:01:20.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll definitely expose the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.77,0:01:24.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right now at this moment, \Nlight pierces the darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.86,0:01:26.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Overcome all limits with \Nyour cool reasoning skills!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.78,0:01:28.82,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A strange case takes \Nplace at a radio station!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.82,0:01:30.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The grinning culprit stands above the law!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.86,0:01:32.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.38,0:01:34.01,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.01,0:01:36.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.96,0:03:23.97,DCEpTitle,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(404,1)}The Radio Questions and Concerns Show \N(Solution Arc)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.48,0:03:21.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Radio Questions and \NConcerns Show, Solution Arc!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.73,0:03:42.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You still think they did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.28,0:03:46.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They really seemed to hate Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.24,0:03:49.66,Ninosuke,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Inuyama Ninosuke (38) \NNichiuri TV Presenter
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:48.66,DCItalic,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I know all about you, Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.17,0:03:55.46,DCItalic,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You're secretly scheming to prevent \Nme from becoming independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.67,0:03:59.13,Mamoru,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Kujirai Mamoru (35) \NNichiuri TV & Radio \NProduction Unit Director
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.88,0:03:58.20,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You don't love radio!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.20,0:03:59.60,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You never have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.10,0:04:03.65,DCItalic,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,You only think of your programs \Nas tools to make yourself rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.65,0:04:05.47,DCItalic,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,You misappropriate them \Nfor your personal use!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.33,0:04:10.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose. It's clear that \Nthey found him disagreeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.56,0:04:13.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But remember what Yashiro Kaede-san said?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:17.06,Kaede,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Yashiro Kaede (32) \NBroadcast Writer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.64,0:04:17.72,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's true that they don't \Nget along with Manda-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:21.99,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,but I can't believe they'd kill \Nhis wife just to get at Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.42,0:04:24.74,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.03,0:04:28.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and eat your \Nfood. Then we're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.17,0:04:34.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wasn't that Okino Yoko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.25,0:04:37.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Yoko-chan's here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.13,0:04:38.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where? Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.93,0:04:41.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This way? That way?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.88,0:04:46.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.18,0:04:54.60,Rie,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Abe Rie (24) \NNichiuri TV & Radio \NProduction Unit AD
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.46,0:04:55.77,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's true that Manda-san was trying to \Nprevent Inuyama-san from becoming independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.35,0:04:59.52,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,But I doubt he'd be able to stop Inuyama-san
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.52,0:05:01.52,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,if he really wanted to quit \Nworking for the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:02.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.81,0:05:06.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kujirai-san didn't get along \Nwith Manda-san either, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.19,0:05:10.81,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Kujirai-san's such a serious person.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:13.83,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,He'd never get along with \Nthe slick Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.17,0:05:16.77,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, he was disgusted with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.52,0:05:20.94,DCItalic,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,That incompetent fool shouldn't \Nbe working in radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.03,0:05:23.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Incompetent?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.56,0:05:28.34,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,It's apparently about a drama Manda-san \Nput on while he was a director.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.84,0:05:31.76,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,But it's an old story, so \NI don't know much about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.96,0:05:34.42,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I remember now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.42,0:05:35.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.51,0:05:39.98,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,I think that old drama was \NYashiro-san's debut work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.26,0:05:41.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.90,0:05:46.42,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,You can read it in this reception area.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.42,0:05:48.26,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be right over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.26,0:05:49.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.11,0:05:55.12,Nichiuri,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.11,0:05:55.12,NichiuriScript,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Radio Drama \NHe Disappeared Without \NSaying Goodbye \NScript Yashiro Kaede \NDirector Manda Teruomi \NProduction Nichiuri TV \N& Radio Production Unit
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.14,0:05:55.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This single drama made Yashiro-san \Nthink she owed Manda-san everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.70,0:06:00.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,while also making Kujirai-san \Nthink he was incompetent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.02,0:06:01.37,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.34,0:06:03.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She's not here either.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.49,0:06:05.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Okino Yoko-chan, where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:08.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Okino Yoko-chan, where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.97,0:06:12.22,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.22,0:06:14.72,Nichiuri2,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.22,0:06:14.72,NichiuriScript,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Radio Drama \NHe Disappeared Without \NSaying Goodbye \NScript Yashiro Kaede \NDirector Manda Teruomi \NProduction Nichiuri TV \N& Radio Production Unit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.46,0:06:16.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.56,0:06:17.95,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.95,0:06:23.41,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan said he'd like \Nto hear a recording of this drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.41,0:06:26.99,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. I'll submit a request \Nto the records department.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.30,0:06:29.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.90,0:06:39.87,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is. Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:44.63,Cast,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Cast \NIsaka Kiko – Adachi Towako
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.29,0:06:44.09,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This name, Adachi Towako...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:47.42,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.00,0:06:50.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They wouldn't have said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:54.64,Cast,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Producer Kamio Yoshitaka
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.99,0:06:58.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.10,0:07:02.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's all I need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.17,0:07:03.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.72,0:07:06.15,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Which means...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.08,0:07:09.15,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, so that's why?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.43,0:07:13.16,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he drank even though \Nhe was about to go on the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.60,0:07:17.63,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,And someone said during \Nthe post show meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.63,0:07:23.17,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,that they wished Manda-san's wife's upstairs \Nneighbor could've heard the show, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:24.17,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.59,0:07:27.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.58,0:07:30.04,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.15,0:07:33.30,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.75,0:07:38.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They used the concern that was submitted \Nby coincidence in their plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.72,0:07:39.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.27,0:07:44.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't I find you, Yoko-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.90,0:07:47.12,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.53,0:07:50.49,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be coincidence that such \Na convenient concern was submitted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.14,0:07:57.49,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,The listener TM-san isn't the \Nvictim Manda Towako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.58,0:08:01.50,Morikawa,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Morikawa Tsugumi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.98,0:08:01.50,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It's someone completely different \Nnamed Morikawa Tsugumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.16,0:08:04.50,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.87,0:08:06.72,DCMain,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.72,0:08:09.51,DCMain,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm Morikawa Tsugumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:13.22,Tsugumi,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Morikawa Tsugumi (32) \NHousewife
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:13.44,DCMain,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What? The famous detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.44,0:08:16.73,DCMain,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What does the famous Mori \NKogoro-san want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:19.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.73,0:08:23.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Once I get the results of the \Ninvestigation I requested...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.09,0:08:26.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You damn brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.86,0:08:27.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.77,0:08:31.28,Yoko,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko in Hawaii
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.14,0:08:31.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yoko-chan couldn't possibly be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.28,0:08:33.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's in Hawaii, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.53,0:08:35.34,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We're leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.63,0:08:38.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I need to use the bathroom first.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.67,0:08:39.95,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.29,0:08:42.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That damn brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.55,0:08:47.96,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Ah, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.66,0:08:49.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.96,0:08:55.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I'm actually still at Nichiuri TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.69,0:08:56.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.58,0:08:59.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.05,0:09:04.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Hello? Hello, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.12,0:09:07.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I feel better now. Should we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.80,0:09:09.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We can't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.11,0:09:09.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.27,0:09:14.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why, but the inspector told \Nme to wait because he was on his way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.77,0:09:17.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And he told me to gather all the staff again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.58,0:09:19.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder why.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.60,0:09:26.08,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,What do the police want now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:29.48,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,The situation's become complicated
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.48,0:09:32.03,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,since they found out the victim \Nwas Manda-san's wife, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.26,0:09:35.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.40,0:09:37.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Mori-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.80,0:09:43.58,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you asked my detectives \Nto bring Manda here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.58,0:09:47.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? You told me to wait—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.02,0:09:51.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Told me to wait for you here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.73,0:09:54.11,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the rumored Sleeping Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.58,0:09:55.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.87,0:10:01.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,in the case of Manda Towako-san's \Nmurder by her husband
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.32,0:10:02.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and suspect Manda Teruomi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.70,0:10:08.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The plot lurking behind it \Nmost likely began a month ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.24,0:10:14.38,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,when Manda-san was brought \Nhere as the new producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.50,0:10:30.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When Manda-san was assigned to \Nbe the new producer of the show,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.59,0:10:35.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inuyama-san, he told you \Nabout his wife then, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.35,0:10:37.78,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.82,0:10:41.78,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,At the welcoming party we were \Nsocially obligated to throw.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.04,0:10:49.29,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I wish my awful wife would just disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.57,0:10:54.94,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I met her the other day about the divorce, \Nand she wouldn't stop complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.94,0:10:59.42,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Something about her obnoxious \Nupstairs neighbor at her apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.42,0:11:02.55,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,That's not my problem, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.22,0:11:05.06,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.47,0:11:10.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When they heard that, the culprit \Ncame up with their plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.29,0:11:17.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They'd murder Manda-san's \Nwife and frame him for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.45,0:11:20.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Yashiro Kaede-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.44,0:11:21.20,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.86,0:11:29.55,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Why would I frame Manda-san \Nwhen I owe him everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.11,0:11:31.16,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.81,0:11:34.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.31,0:11:38.31,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,When we showed this photo you sent us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.31,0:11:41.34,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,to the residents of Manda \NTowako-san's apartment building,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.94,0:11:45.01,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,several of them remembered you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.01,0:11:48.26,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They said half a month ago \Nyou were asking around
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.26,0:11:51.10,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,about Manda Towako-san's upstairs \Nneighbor Kijima Kumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.34,0:11:57.61,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,They said they told you that Kijima-san \Ngoes barhopping every Friday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.83,0:12:02.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you decided to \Ndo it on a Friday, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.52,0:12:08.49,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Just because I asked about Kijima-san, \Nthat doesn't make me the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.85,0:12:12.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's also the radio show submission.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.94,0:12:15.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You forged that, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.18,0:12:18.02,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.01,0:12:25.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I checked in with your friend \NMorikawa Tsugumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.44,0:12:31.64,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I heard from Yashiro-san \Nthat she asked you to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.98,0:12:37.17,DCItalic,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What? Oh, Kaede admitted it herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.67,0:12:40.94,DCItalic,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,She made me promise not to tell anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.85,0:12:46.16,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,We don't get enough interesting submissions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.37,0:12:50.04,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I can write the submission myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:54.54,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,but if it's chosen, the \Nstation calls the listener.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.96,0:12:57.24,DCItalic,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,So you want me to pretend I wrote it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.68,0:12:59.54,DCItalic,TSUGUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. You can count on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.99,0:13:01.67,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.26,0:13:06.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You asked Morikawa Tsugumi-san \Nbecause her initials are TM.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.54,0:13:09.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The same as Manda Towako-san's.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.88,0:13:14.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was necessary to involve Kijima Kumi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.05,0:13:17.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Using Morikawa-san's name,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.00,0:13:21.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you wrote a fictitious submission \Nthat would make Kijima Kumi-san
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.07,0:13:24.28,HelpLetter,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what to do about the crazy woman \Nliving in the apartment directly above mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.50,0:13:24.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,believe it was Manda Towako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.64,0:13:29.53,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing will happen if this \Ndoesn't get picked up first.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:32.54,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I hope they decide to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.02,0:13:38.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Once the submission arrived at the station, \Nyou selected it for Friday's show.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.72,0:13:42.50,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,As the show organizer,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.50,0:13:46.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,it was your responsibility to \Nselect submissions for the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.77,0:13:51.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday, on the day of your crime, you \Ngave a plausible excuse to make me drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.91,0:13:56.64,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,They say Mori-san performs better \Nwhen he's had a drink or two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.17,0:13:59.40,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You got me drunk and worked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.91,0:13:59.87,TheBest,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(460,460)}Mori-san, you're the best!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.21,0:14:02.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After inciting me to make rude \Ncomments during the show,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.61,0:14:05.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,during the post show meeting...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.11,0:14:11.06,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I wish the woman living \Nabove Manda-san's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.06,0:14:13.12,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,could've heard today's show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.41,0:14:16.12,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,That's when I had an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.48,0:14:18.62,DCItalic,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,You've gotta strike when the iron's hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.52,0:14:27.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You incited Kijima Kumi-san to \Nfight with Manda Towako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:30.17,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,They don't even know \Nthey're being manipulated.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.17,0:14:32.64,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It's all going exactly according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.90,0:14:35.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And after all that scheming...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.70,0:14:39.77,DCMain,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want? It's \Nthe middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.86,0:14:58.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-kun, even if she plotted to \Nframe Manda-san for his wife's murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:03.04,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,why did she need to involve Kijima Kumi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.25,0:15:05.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Because even though he has a motive,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.31,0:15:10.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,not having an alibi wasn't a compelling \Nenough reason to suspect him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.78,0:15:15.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inciting Kijima-san to attack his wife
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.22,0:15:19.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,guaranteed suspicion would fall on Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.60,0:15:24.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, Kijima-san would \Nbe suspected for a while,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.32,0:15:30.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but her alibi would be verified since \Nshe spent her Fridays barhopping.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.68,0:15:35.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But the police were struggling \Nto verify her alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.58,0:15:38.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's when you asked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.35,0:15:40.74,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, I have a request.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.74,0:15:44.83,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Please prove Kijima Kumi-san's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.26,0:15:49.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted suspicion to be shifted
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.03,0:15:52.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,from Kijima-san to Manda-san \Nwas quickly as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.72,0:15:56.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You had me come on as a guest
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.43,0:16:02.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,in case the police took too long to \Nverify Kijima-san's alibi, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.33,0:16:06.19,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So everything was calculated?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.51,0:16:08.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't need to do anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.15,0:16:11.70,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Kijima-san's alibi was verified.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.00,0:16:14.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And we suspected Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.99,0:16:17.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Yashiro-san wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.28,0:16:23.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,However, Conan suspected \NInuyama-san and Kujirai-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.53,0:16:27.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so you hastily denied that possibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.72,0:16:29.72,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,That's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.72,0:16:34.21,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that they don't get \Nalong with Manda-san, but
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.85,0:16:39.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,because you were desperate \Nto frame Manda-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.88,0:16:44.14,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,Everything you're saying is just speculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.81,0:16:47.39,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt you've noticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.82,0:16:50.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but you keep repeating a certain action.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.03,0:16:55.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When suspicion fell on Manda-san \Nbecause of the CD...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.89,0:16:57.78,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.03,0:16:59.59,DCItalic,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,How did it go, Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.04,0:17:02.24,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. About that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.77,0:17:12.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When we learned Kijima-san was innocent, \Nand Manda-san was the only suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.97,0:17:16.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And when Manda-san was taken away...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.48,0:17:20.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You touched the band-aid \Non the back of your neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.82,0:17:25.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Every time things went according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.16,0:17:32.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You must've been unconsciously worried \Nabout the mark left there by your crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.82,0:17:36.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. The sample sent for DNA testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.40,0:17:38.48,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Left under the victim's fingernails...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.48,0:17:39.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.17,0:17:45.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In her final struggle, Manda Towako-san \Nscratched the back of her killer's neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.91,0:17:47.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong, Yashiro-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.22,0:17:55.20,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd won.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.98,0:17:59.00,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I never stood a chance \Nagainst the great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.44,0:18:04.77,DCMain,RIE,0000,0000,0000,,Yashiro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.20,0:18:10.77,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,B-But why? I thought you owed me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.16,0:18:13.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It was hate, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.48,0:18:15.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,For Manda-san and Towako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.09,0:18:20.06,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hate? Over what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.06,0:18:22.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When I asked about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.35,0:18:26.16,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She was a rising talent?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.66,0:18:28.33,DCItalic,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.14,0:18:31.19,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But your answer was strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.68,0:18:33.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan, the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.17,0:18:35.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.56,0:18:42.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Manda-san's wife's maiden \Nname was Adachi Towako-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.18,0:18:47.68,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Seven years ago, she played the \Nleading role in your debut work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.68,0:18:47.68,Cast,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Cast \NIsaka Kiko – Adachi Towako
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.97,0:18:51.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But you tried to hide that,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.89,0:18:54.35,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,which means it must have something \Nto do with the crux of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.32,0:18:58.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,"He Disappeared Without Saying Goodbye."
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.38,0:19:01.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a very good script.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.60,0:19:02.96,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.96,0:19:06.81,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a masterful depiction of a person's \Nfeelings for the lover they suddenly lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.81,0:19:08.33,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,Truly a rare masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.79,0:19:13.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But once it became a drama, you \Ncouldn't stand to listen to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.11,0:19:17.13,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,Because the director didn't \Nunderstand any of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.13,0:19:22.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And Adachi Towako-san's \Ninfantile performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.44,0:19:25.20,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,It was truly awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.20,0:19:27.60,DCMain,INUYAMA,0000,0000,0000,,Worse than a school play.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.86,0:19:29.90,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.90,0:19:36.19,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,I told the producer from the \Nstart that she couldn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.39,0:19:37.57,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.68,0:19:43.17,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I checked with Kamio Yoshitaka-san, \Nthe producer at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.80,0:19:48.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who ignored the opposition \Nand cast her in the lead role.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.09,0:19:54.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You were already dating Adachi Towako-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.92,0:19:57.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and intended it to be a present for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:19:58.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.36,0:20:01.57,DCMain,KUJIRAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's a true misappropriation of a show!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.02,0:20:06.47,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,But everyone does it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.95,0:20:09.97,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yashiro-san must've been frustrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.54,0:20:13.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Not because it was her debut work,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.28,0:20:18.01,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but because this work depicting \Nthe loss of a loved one
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.67,0:20:20.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,is your own experience, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.38,0:20:28.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't have been able \Nto write it otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.52,0:20:35.18,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Manda-san, your and Towako-san's selfishness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.18,0:20:41.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,ruined a work that was \Nimportant to Yashiro-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.48,0:20:42.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,But, Mori-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.41,0:20:46.64,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,why would she act on a \Nseven-year-old grudge now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:51.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yashiro-san probably hadn't \Nbeen holding a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.60,0:20:56.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But one month ago, Manda-san was \Nassigned to be the show's producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.72,0:21:03.56,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It had been seven years, \Nbut nothing had changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.56,0:21:09.73,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,His superficial glibness and misappropriation \Nof programs had only increased!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.85,0:21:13.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That old frustration returned,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.20,0:21:17.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and she decided to seek \Nrevenge on the couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.71,0:21:23.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She used a sedative at the \Nstaff drinking party last night
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.41,0:21:26.85,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,to make Manda-san tired so he'd go home,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.85,0:21:28.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,ruining his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.16,0:21:32.69,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After that, she headed to \NManda Towako-san's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.93,0:21:37.06,DCItalic,TOWAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want? It's \Nthe middle of the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.53,0:21:54.36,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,I poured my soul into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.85,0:21:58.89,DCMain,KAEDE,0000,0000,0000,,It was so awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.03,0:23:28.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, I'm beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.75,0:23:32.43,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think I'm fit for radio.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.64,0:23:35.79,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I'm too handsome.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.76,0:23:43.29,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This old man doesn't have \Na concern in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.00,0:23:48.94,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Let me take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.60,0:23:52.38,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but is this book yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.14,0:23:55.58,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, it belongs to my husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.07,0:23:59.26,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,You stole this from Mizutani-san's \Nhouse, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.26,0:24:00.33,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.79,0:24:04.96,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Tamaki Yujiro-san, could you come \Ndown to the station with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.21,0:24:06.21,DCMain,AYUMI,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.21,0:24:07.81,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Hand cream?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.81,0:24:08.66,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Whistling Bookstore 2
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.88,0:24:14.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Whistling Bookstore 2!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Rare Book
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.83,0:24:33.12,DCMain,MANDA,0000,0000,0000,,You're listening to "Next Conan's Hint."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.12,0:24:34.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A rare book!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:36.12,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What's a rare book?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.12,0:24:37.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}A book that's extremely difficult to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.86,0:24:39.55,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Like Detective Mori.
